name: Helium
etymology: Loanword. Homophonic with 亥, meaning 'astrological pig'.

name: Boron
etymology: Classic term. Homophonic with 朋, meaning 'friend'.
notes: Originally used to mean borax, 硼砂 (péngshā).

name: Carbon
etymology: Classic term. Modified version of 炭 (tàn), meaning coal.

name: Nitrogen
etymology: Modern term. Homophonic with 淡, meaning 'bland' or 'dilute'.
notes: 淡 is composed of one 氵water radical  and two 火 fire radicals. Confusingly, the character for nitrogen drops the water radical, making '氮' appear to be composed of '炎气' (yánqì), where 炎 means 'blazing hot' or 'inflammation', neither of which makes sense to describe nitrogen.
Another early translation of nitrogen was 硝气 (xiāoqì), where 硝 means 'niter'.

name: Oxygen
etymology: Modern term. Homophonic with 养, meaning 'life-nurturing'.
notes: Short for 养气 (yǎngqì). The phrase '养气' is still in use nowadays, but typically in a more spiritual sense; 气 (qì) can also refer to the traditional notion of life energy, and so 养气 is basically self-care.

The character 氧 actually contains '羊' (yáng), meaning 'goat'. This substitution is easier to write, and works on multiple levels. 羊 and 养 look similar, they're pronounced similarly, and goats 羊 happen to be an example of the lifeforms which are nourished 养 by oxygen.

name: Aluminium
etymology: Loanword. Homophonic with 吕, meaning 'Lu  (musical note/name)'.

name: Silicon
notes: Other early attempts to translate 'silicon' included: 玻精 (bōjīng), meaning 'glass essence'; 矽 (xī), homophone of 夕, meaning 'dusk' and the very silly full transliteration '夕里西恩 (xīlǐxīēn)'.

name: Titanium
etymology: Loanword. Homophonic with 太, meaning 'very big'.

name: Germanium
etymology: Loanword. Homophonic with 者, meaning 'person of'.

name: Rubidium
etymology: Loanword. Homophonic with 如, meaning 'like such as'.

name: Palladium
etymology: Loanword. Homophonic with 把, meaning 'cling to'.

name: Indium
etymology: Loanword. Homophonic with 因, meaning 'because of'.

name: Tellurium
etymology: Loanword. Homophonic with 帝, meaning 'god emperor'.

name: Actinium
etymology: Loanword. Homophonic with 阿, meaning 'ā (name prefix)'.

name: Rutherfordium
etymology: Loanword. Homophonic with 卢, meaning 'rice bowl'.

name: Copernicium
etymology: Loanword. Homophonic with 哥, meaning 'older brother'.
notes: Copernicus is transliterated as 哥白尼 (Gēbáiní)

name: Moscovium
etymology: Loanword. Homophonic with 莫, meaning 'do not'.
